WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.900
AI can generate millions of possible materials, simulate them in microseconds,

2
00:00:03.900 --> 00:00:06.500
and send robots to synthesize them around the clock.

3
00:00:07.240 --> 00:00:08.220
So what is scarce now?

4
00:00:08.900 --> 00:00:09.420
Not ideas.

5
00:00:10.140 --> 00:00:10.780
Not compute.

6
00:00:11.500 --> 00:00:13.300
The scarce resource is believing the result.

7
00:00:14.100 --> 00:00:17.520
Google DeepMind reported 380,000 stable crystal predictions.

8
00:00:18.320 --> 00:00:22.820
By late 2023, only 736 had been independently synthesized.

9
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:25.320
That is zero point two percent.

10
00:00:25.320 --> 00:00:27.540
Every false positive wastes lab weeks.

11
00:00:28.180 --> 00:00:31.500
Every false negative can bury a climate material we needed yesterday.

12
00:00:32.340 --> 00:00:35.767
Lupine sits between prediction and synthesis—not replacing generators or

13
00:00:35.767 --> 00:00:37.480
simulators, but checking their work.

14
00:00:38.200 --> 00:00:41.992
It measures systematic model error, corrects that error at runtime, and proves

15
00:00:41.992 --> 00:00:44.180
which claims a laboratory can actually trust.

16
00:00:44.920 --> 00:00:46.100
The moat has three parts.

17
00:00:46.900 --> 00:00:50.550
First: a measured error field, anchored by standard observables—not another

18
00:00:50.550 --> 00:00:53.080
neural net that needs retraining for every material.

19
00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:58.140
Second: 77 build-locked Lean 4 theorems, with zero unproven shortcuts.

20
00:00:59.160 --> 00:01:03.240
Third: a LAMMPS runtime overlay that works beside tools like C-H-G net and MACE.

21
00:01:04.000 --> 00:01:06.640
Today, it adds 15.6 percent overhead.

22
00:01:07.280 --> 00:01:09.170
Compiled, the target is below one percent.

23
00:01:09.700 --> 00:01:11.700
And the proof layer is not decorative.

24
00:01:12.580 --> 00:01:16.698
Lean once rejected a claim that passed statistical filtering, changing 27

25
00:01:16.698 --> 00:01:17.600
successes to 26.

26
00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:21.887
That is the product in miniature: trustworthy infrastructure has to catch its

27
00:01:21.887 --> 00:01:24.540
own mistakes—and say no when the evidence does not hold.

28
00:01:25.240 --> 00:01:27.500
Each screening campaign adds measured bias data.

29
00:01:28.240 --> 00:01:30.080
Each experiment tightens the next prediction.

30
00:01:30.840 --> 00:01:32.820
Each theorem expands the verified boundary.

31
00:01:33.580 --> 00:01:36.320
What is proven today is the field for face-centered-cubic metals.

32
00:01:37.180 --> 00:01:40.923
Extending it to other crystal families—and securing industrial validation—is

33
00:01:40.923 --> 00:01:41.760
still work ahead.

34
00:01:42.460 --> 00:01:43.840
That honesty is part of the moat.

35
00:01:44.480 --> 00:01:46.560
So this is not a bet on one magic material.

36
00:01:47.180 --> 00:01:50.630
It is a bet on the trust layer that makes discovery more capital-efficient:

37
00:01:50.630 --> 00:01:54.218
fewer predictions, better defended, reaching the lab before the climate window

38
00:01:54.218 --> 00:01:54.540
closes.
